metadata.name: Resilience #171
metadata.description:
In this project i tried to portray the struggles and hardships of life in a modern era. The use of bold and gloomy shades of black, brown and gray creates an overwhelming sense of oppression and heaviness. Yet amidst the chaos, tiny specks of light in the form of vibrant, bright colors like red, gold, yellow, green and blue symbolize hope and resilience.

The texture is heavily layered, suggesting the layers of difficulties that must be faced and overcome in life.

Overall, this canvas captures the essence of a hard life, but also highlights the triumphs of the human spirit in the face of adversity.

metadata.name: Bound #176
metadata.description:
Knots bind and hold, mark time, and unite. But the power of a well-tied knot isn't only to fasten – it also symbolizes how tightly one holds their pledges. Whether a commitment to a partner, community, or oneself – the longevity of a deeply held bond is often marked with a symbol of passing time, like knots tied in a rope.

Let these ropes remind us of the binds we hold – new ones, lengthy ones, unbreakable ones, and even those we’ve had to untie. In plain view, these knots invite us to contemplate what our bonds mean to us, and to see them anew.

---

metadata.name: Sparsely Populated Grid #155
metadata.description:
“Sparsely Populated Grid” is the result of an architect’s fascination with Cartographies and a crypto-enthusiast love for Neo Punk aesthetics. The first sketch, drawn by hand with Procreate, was made in October 2021.

This is an exploration on the field of Generative Cartographies, an abstract diagrammatic representation of a randomly generated area within the virtual IPFS world. Everything starts with an GRID of varying sizes and angles, subsequently POPULATED by a random number of forms. But, how to populate the grid? SPARSELY, of course, with just the right amount of superpositions.

The algorithm produces varying compositions of fourteen different forms, with seven possible mixes and ten colour palettes. Movement, made possible by its generative digital nature, follows sinusoidal patterns, as if the forms breathed and danced to an unheard music.

Besides, they never forget to celebrate birthdays.


// INTERACTIVITY

- CLICK or SPACEBAR to stop movement.
- UP and DOWN ARROWS to Disable/Enable graphic elements such as texts (wink).
- LEFT and RIGHT ARROWS (when stopped) to Move frames back and forth.
- Press 1 for a low-res PNG.
- Press 2 for a medium-res PNG (3x).
- Press 3 for a hi-res PNG (6x).
- Press G for Glitch (low-res).
- Press P for PixelArt (low-res).

If you want a different resolution, you can also add ?&res=xxx to the url to get your desired output. Then simply Right-Click SAVE the canvas -- experimental

metadata.name: A Pocket Full of Wonder #63
metadata.description:
"A Pocket Full of Wonder" invites you to embark on a journey where the boundaries between technology and art are blurred. 

Here, machine-generated images serve as a foundation for a vibrant and dynamic world of code-driven art. This union of artificial intelligence and creative coding evokes a sense of wonder and discovery, as each piece reveals the beauty that can be born from the interplay of technology and art. 

With "A Pocket Full of Wonder", we explore the limitless possibilities that emerge when we allow technology to augment and enhance our artistic visions.
